# Marketing OS — environment variables
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values. .env is gitignored so secrets stay local.
# This file (`env`, no extension, no leading dot) is committed as a template so anyone cloning
# the repo can see what they need to set without it being hidden as a dotfile.
#
# Only EXA_API_KEY is required for the 15-minute tour. Other MCPs are commented out in .mcp.json
# and only need their env vars set when you uncomment those MCPs.
# Full 12-connector setup guide: .claude/connections.md

# === REQUIRED ===

# Exa API key — for web search + page fetch via the Exa MCP
# Get yours at: https://exa.ai (free tier OK)
EXA_API_KEY=

# === OPTIONAL — uncomment as you wire each MCP ===

# Google Analytics 4
# Property ID is in your GA4 admin panel (looks like "properties/123456789")
# Credentials JSON is from a Google Cloud service account with GA4 access
# GA4_PROPERTY_ID=
# GA4_CREDENTIALS_JSON=

# Google Search Console
# Site URL exactly matches the verified property in GSC (e.g., "sc-domain:yourdomain.com")
# GSC_SITE_URL=
# GSC_CREDENTIALS_JSON=

# Granola — meeting transcripts
# Get API key from your Granola account settings
# GRANOLA_API_KEY=

# Slack — team notifications + channel reads
# Bot token starts with "xoxb-"; install Slack app via api.slack.com first
# SLACK_BOT_TOKEN=

# Firecrawl — heavy web crawl
# Get API key from firecrawl.dev
# FIRECRAWL_API_KEY=
